CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 10, 1967, pg. 17, reads: "Prize Winners - This quartet were among the twenty five selected by judges as wearing the most authentic African costumes at the AKA 'Ajoyo'.  Left to right: Ann Bennell, Agnes Curry, Marion Saunders and Gelora Wilson."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Ann Bennell, Agnes Curry, unknown man and woman, Marion Saunders, and Gelora Wilson, wearing African style clothing, posed in Flying Carpet for Alpha Kappa Alpha "Ajoyo"
